# Cursor Rules for WelineFramework

Read `AI-ENTRY.md`, then follow `dev/ai/global-constraints.md` as the single source of repository-wide AI rules.

Cursor-specific always-on summaries live in `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` and mirror selected rules from `dev/ai/global-constraints.md`; if they conflict, `dev/ai/global-constraints.md` wins.

Additional legacy Cursor protocols remain reference-only unless explicitly triggered by task markers:

- `dev/ai/rules/agent-supervisor-protocol.md` when files contain `@AgentID` or `[SUPERVISOR_TASK]`
- `dev/ai/rules/QUALITY_SYSTEM_CURSOR_RULES.md`
- `dev/ai/rules/multi-agent-protocol.md`
- `dev/ai/rules/efficiency_rules.md`

Quick commands and skill routing are maintained in `AI-ENTRY.md` and `dev/ai/skills/_index.md`.
